Vlad main here, D4, currently #288 best Vladimir, used to be #105 but stopped playing ranked for a while (not being arrogant, just mentioning this to increase the validity of my suggestions).
Runes: flat pen reds, flat armor or hp per level yellows, flat cdr blues, 2 ap quints and one flat cdr quint.
Summoner spells: I always pick ghost and flash. I never pick teleport on Vladimir.
Masteries: 0/18/12. Make sure you pick the mastery that reduces the cd of summoner spells.
Keystone mastery: Depends. If you pick teleport instead of ghost, pick stormraider. If you pick ghost, pick thunderlord like I do.
Builds: 

1) If the enemy team has 2 ap champs (mid, support): {{item:3065}} {{item:3152}} {{item:3157}} {{item:3047}} {{item:3089}} {{item:3135}} 

2) If the enemy team has more than 2 ap champs or when it has 2 ap champs without counting in the support: {{item:3065}} {{item:3102}} {{item:3157}} {{item:3047}} {{item:3089}} {{item:3135}} 

3) If the enemy team is full ad: {{item:3157}} {{item:3158}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3089}} {{item:3152}} {{item:3135}} 

As you can see, you will always buy {{item:3089}} {{item:3157}} . In some instances I have found myself using build #2 for the senario of build #1 because the enemy mage was a threat (for example a fed enemy {{champion:69}} ) and one mr item wasn't enough for me. But you can figure it out. Hope I helped!
